<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[264,1323,283,550]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,442,283,309]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Distinguished from all congeners by possessing a unique color pattern on the caudal fin in males, consisting of three to five light blue stripes crossing the fin, parallel to fin rays, alternating with subdistal rounded light blue spots (
<emphasis box="[1041,1072,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">vs.</emphasis>
never a similar color pattern). Similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[492,607,404,429]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="notatus">
<emphasis box="[492,607,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. notatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[621,747,404,429]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="stellatus">
<emphasis box="[621,747,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. stellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[762,851,404,429]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rufus">
<emphasis box="[762,851,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. rufus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[865,970,404,429]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="similis">
<emphasis box="[865,970,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. similis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[984,1133,404,429]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="trilineatus">
<emphasis box="[984,1133,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. trilineatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1148,1266,404,429]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="auratus">
<emphasis box="[1148,1266,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. auratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[264,402,444,469]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ocellatus">
<emphasis box="[264,402,444,469]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">S. ocellatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and distinguished from all other species of the genus by having the frontal squamation A­patterned (vs. E­patterned); differs from these species in having a broad basihyal (width about 
<number box="[525,555,524,550]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="85.0">85</number>
% of basihyal length, vs. 
<number box="[853,932,524,550]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="62.5" valueMax="75.0" valueMin="50.0">50–75</number>
%).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
